<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - TACHOMETER INPUT
        CIRCUITS - CORRECTIVE ACTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CORRECTIVE ACTION</title>
        <para>If the tachometer doesn't work and:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The Speedometer/Tachometer Self-Test does not indicate a defect, perform Testing Circuit
                97AR (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e125_403.xml" xrefid="ef12518158">3.165</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).If the self-test revealed a defect, follow service manual recommended corrective action.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The Tach Buffer KOER test
                <emph type="bold">does not</emph>
                set a fault code, then check circuit 97AR between VPM connector (381) and I/P connector (27) for open or
                short (high or low) circuit by performing Testing Circuit 97AR (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e125_403.xml" xrefid="ef12518158">3.165</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the Tach Buffer KOER test
                <emph type="bold">does set</emph>
                Flash code 233, perform Testing ECM/VPM Tachometer Circuit (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e125_404.xml" xrefid="ef12518159">3.166</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk document="e125_404.xml" xrefid="ef12518160">3.167</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
